{
  "stem": "20088.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then my father, who lived not in Amsterdam but in the south of Holland, and he said to us, well, it doesn't really matter if you live in Amsterdam or Brussels, because for me it would be just the same distance to travel.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was coming then most weekends to visit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So once my father came, he brought money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he found us a boarding house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had one room there with my brother and my mother and me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when my father came weekend, we hired another little room where my mother and my father could stay.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was very primitive, actually.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had to go straightaway to a French school, which-- as I said, I didn't like school anyway.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was of course horrendous because they were not use to-- there were very few refugees at this time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had no instructions what to do with refugee children, to teach us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they just didn't really take any notice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just spoke to me in French and gave me a seat, and that was it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I couldn't follow anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't know what it-- what was happening.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And after a few weeks, there was a dictation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I had to write down-- and French, of course, is a difficult language to write anyway.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whatever I wrote, every word was wrong, of course.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the next day when they got the works back, with the mistakes underlined in red, the teacher showed my work to the class with everything, of course, in red, because there was not a single word correct, to show how stupid I was.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I think about this now, how people could do things like that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's just unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
